==English==

===Pronunciation===
*mē'diə, /ˈmiːdiə/, /<tt>"mi:di@</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-iːdiə|Rhymes: -iːdiə]]

===Noun===
'''media''' (''plural:'' '''[[mediae]]''')

# {{italbrac|Anatomy}} the middle layer of the wall of a blood vessel or lymph vessel which is composed of connective and muscular tissue.  (tunica media, between the tunica interna and tunica externa).

====Usage notes====
Not to be confused with [[medium]].

===Noun===
'''media''' (''plural of'' '''[[medium]]''')

# Formats for presenting information.
#: ''Collage is a form of [[mixed-media|mixed-'''media''']] artwork.''
# {{italbrac|with a definite article}} The journalists and other professionals who compose the mass communication industry.

====Usage notes====
Although correctly plural, its use as a mass noun with a singular verb is under continuing debate.

